# SceneSetupSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
One-shot scene builder. Returns early until both SandboxConfigSingletonComponent and
ResourceMapSingletonComponent are present. On the first ready frame it creates the input-reactive
scene camera, the demo sprite, and the world-space labels (a title, an instructions label, and a
tagged input-readout label), emitting a SceneTransformRequestOneFrameComponent to seed each one's
world transform (position-only for the camera). It also emits a LoadLayoutEvent to load the UI layout
and creates SceneReadySingletonComponent as its run-once guard.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Font/texture/layout ids for the scene; guard (returns early if absent) |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Guard only: ensures the layout load will resolve |
| SceneReadySingletonComponent | read | Run-once guard |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| OrthographicCameraComponent | add (deferred) | Input-reactive scene camera (CameraSystem then drives it) |
| SpriteComponent | add (deferred) | The demo sub-texture sprite |
| LabelComponent | add (deferred) | Title, instructions and the input-readout label |
| SceneTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Seeds the world transform for the camera, sprite and labels |
| InputReadoutTagComponent | add (deferred) | Marks the readout label for InputReadoutSystem |
| LoadLayoutEvent | add (deferred) | Emitted once to load the UI layout |
| SceneReadySingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Run-once guard |
